    "image": "/images/posts/getting-started-with-nextjs/hero.jpg",
    "content": "# Getting Started with Next.js 15\n\nNext.js 15 brings exciting new features and improvements that make building React applications even more powerful and efficient.\n\n![Next.js 15 Dashboard](/images/posts/getting-started-with-nextjs/hero.jpg)\n\n## What's New in Next.js 15\n\nNext.js 15 introduces several game-changing features:\n\n### 1. Turbopack (Stable)\nThe new bundler is now stable and provides significantly faster build times:\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev --turbo\n```\n\n### 2. Enhanced App Router\nThe App Router continues to evolve with better performance and developer experience.\n\n![App Router Structure](/images/posts/getting-started-with-nextjs/app-router-diagram.svg)\n\n### 3. Server Components by Default\nServer Components are now the default, providing better performance and SEO.\n\n## Getting Started\n\nTo create a new Next.js 15 project:\n\n```bash\nnpx create-next-app@latest my-app\ncd my-app\nnpm run dev\n```\n\n## Key Features\n\n- **File-based routing**: Automatic routing based on your file structure\n- **Server-side rendering**: Built-in SSR and SSG capabilities\n- **API routes**: Full-stack applications with built-in API endpoints\n- **TypeScript support**: First-class TypeScript integration\n\n## Conclusion\n\nNext.js 15 continues to be the go-to framework for React applications, offering improved performance and developer experience. Whether you're building a simple blog or a complex web application, Next.js provides the tools you need to succeed.\n\nHappy coding! ",
